Quantitative Feedback    Question Mean S.Dev.     The instructor presented the course in an organized manner. 4.56 0.57   The instructor stimulated my thinking. 4.35 0.79   The instructor evaluated my work fairly. 4.33 0.66   The instructor made good use of examples to clarify concepts. 4.54 0.67   The instructor maintained a good learning environment. 4.47 0.64   The instructor was accessible to students. 4.45 0.60   Express your judgment of the instructor&rsquo;s overall teaching effectiveness. 4.08 0.78     53 respondents totaling 47% of registered students; 5-point scale from 1 [hardly at all/ineffective] to 5 [to a very high degree/excellent].   Selected Qualitative Feedback  &ldquo;Robbie is friendly and shows great passion for the subject. He is not alienating, and has only increased my passion for philosophy. A remarkable professor. Also, amazingly lively for a 9 AM class.&rdquo;
&ldquo;He was very approachable and accessible. He is a very good professor.&rdquo;
&ldquo;The lectures were very organized and I loved that the lecture notes were always posted on CourseWeb in advance so that I could focus more on what Dr. Howton was saying while adding extra notes I felt I needed. He seems very passionate about what he does and provides really good examples to clarify sometimes confusing topics.&rdquo;
&ldquo;He commanded his lectures extremely well. He spoke strongly and clearly. He never seemed to rush through his notes which covered the material so well that it almost entirely eliminated the need for references beyond the readings. And the readings themselves charted an incredibly ordered and logical coarse [sic] through out the entire semester such that, now at the end, everything we&rsquo;ve learned has led seamlessly from one place to the next, culminating in the most interesting and complex material.&rdquo;
&ldquo;He was never hard to approach and always polite and patient when explaining concepts.&rdquo;

